            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and<strong> remaining red onion</strong> into wedges, then separate the wedges into petals</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion petals </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to brown and soften</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
