            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the onion is cooking, chop the <strong>green chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in half, deseed, and slice finely</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ground turmeric</strong>,<strong> fenugreek</strong>, <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong> and <strong>black mustard seeds</strong> to a bowl</p><p>Add 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]<strong> </span>vegetable oil</strong>, 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]<strong> </span>cold water</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and stir it all together – this is your <strong>spice paste</strong></p>",
